ANTHRAX - KAZAKHSTAN (04): (AQMOLA) CATTLE, HUMAN, RESOLVED
***********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 4 Sep 2019
Source: AKIpress News Agency (Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan) [edited]
https://akipress.com/news:624646:Anthrax_quarantine_lifted_in_Akmola_region/


[The] quarantine declared on 17 Aug 2019 in the village of Olginka of Akmola region due to the anthrax outbreak has been lifted, the Ministry of Agriculture of Kazakhstan reported.

"After disinfection of the village, no more precursors of disease were found, which confirmed the results of the examination. The new cases of animal infection and their die-off have not been registered. To date, the epizootic situation is stable and under the control of [the] veterinary service of the region," the statement says.

According to the regional health department, new cases of anthrax infection among the population were not detected.

Olginka village was quarantined since 17 Aug 2019 after [the] hospitalization of 5 residents with the suspected anthrax. They were later diagnosed [with] anthrax. The reason for infection was slaughtering of a cow without veterinary certification.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The event was described in postings 20190819.6629720 and 20190820.6632097, dated 19 and 20 Aug 2019; the single case in a cow was confirmed by PCR. Please refer to Mod.MHJ's commentaries in both mentioned postings. He concluded: "I wish we could all be as efficient as the veterinary diagnostic team in Astana".

According to Kazakhstan's annual OIE report, during 2018 the country suffered 2 human anthrax cases and 2 outbreaks in cattle (3 dead animals). Wide-scale preventive annual vaccinations in animals were applied, including 7 908 931 in cattle, 23 817 169 in sheep/goats, 2 044 554 in equines and 190 838 in camels. - Mod.AS

